images.title: Wheels up in Beijing
images.caption: Wheels up in Beijing
images.desc: Last Wednesday, 25 September, China officially opened the Daxing International Airport in Beijing. Constructed to alleviate pressure on the city's existing airport, Beijing Capital International, the bright orange starfish lookalike took more than four years to construct. And travellers, hold onto your hats, because Daxing International will connect to China's capital city via high-speed train that travels at top speeds of more than 200 mph.
